## 📊 Kubernetes Monitoring with Prometheus & Grafana

### 🧠 Why Monitoring is Required

Deploying applications to Kubernetes is only the first step.

Once applications are running, operators need visibility into:

Application health
Resource utilization
Pod failures
CPU and Memory consumption
Cluster performance
Alerting and troubleshooting

Without monitoring, issues may go unnoticed until users are impacted.

Monitoring tools help engineers proactively identify problems and maintain application reliability.

### 🧠 Core Concept

Monitoring in Kubernetes typically combines:

• Prometheus → Collects and stores metrics
• Grafana → Visualizes metrics through dashboards
• kube-state-metrics → Exposes Kubernetes object metrics
• Alertmanager → Sends alerts when issues occur

Together they provide complete cluster visibility.

