### Key Learnings

• Prometheus is the standard monitoring solution for Kubernetes

• Grafana provides visualization for Prometheus metrics

• Prometheus stores metrics as time-series data

• kube-state-metrics provides detailed Kubernetes object metrics

• Prometheus uses a pull-based scraping model

• Helm simplifies Prometheus and Grafana deployment

• Applications must expose a /metrics endpoint for monitoring

• Grafana dashboards provide real-time cluster visibility

• Monitoring should include both infrastructure and application metrics

• Alertmanager enables proactive incident response

• Monitoring is a critical component of production Kubernetes environments

### 💡 Final Insight

Prometheus, Grafana, kube-state-metrics, and Alertmanager together form a complete Kubernetes observability stack.

By monitoring both cluster infrastructure and application-level metrics, teams can quickly detect issues, improve reliability, and maintain production-ready Kubernetes environments.

